President Barack Obama has proclaimed December 7th as National Pearl Harbor Remembrance Day. This day commemorates the attack on Pearl Harbor in 1941, where more than 2,400 Americans lost their lives. The proclamation honors the bravery and sacrifice of those who served during World War II and encourages Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities. The President also urges federal agencies and interested organizations to fly the flag at half-staff in honor of the fallen patriots.